          <h5 class="w3-opacity"><b>Extracting Stock Data Using Web Scraping</b></h5>
          <h6 class="w3-text-teal"><i class="fa fa-github fa-fw w3-margin-right"></i><a href="https://github.com/D3xt3r7/Python-" target="_blank">GitHub</a></h6>
          <p>- Demonstrates web scraping to extract stock data (e.g., Netflix) using requests and BeautifulSoup, creating a pandas DataFrame with metrics (Date, Open, High, Low, Close, Volume) and comparing with pd.read_html data.</p>
          <p>- Dependencies: pandas, requests, bs4, html5lib, lxml, plotly.</p>
          <hr>
