          <h6 class="w3-text-teal"><i class="fa fa-github fa-fw w3-margin-right"></i><a href="https://github.com/D3xt3r7/Python-" target="_blank">GitHub</a></h6>
          <p>- Uses yfinance to download historical stock data (e.g., Apple) and visualizes it with matplotlib, including dividend data and JSON file handling.</p>
          <p>- Dependencies: yfinance, matplotlib, pandas.</p>
          <hr>
          <h5 class="w3-opacity"><b>The GDP Scraper</b></h5>
          <h6 class="w3-text-teal"><i class="fa fa-github fa-fw w3-margin-right"></i><a href="https://github.com/D3xt3r7/Python-" target="_blank">GitHub</a></h6>
          <p>- Scrapes GDP data from a Wikipedia archive using pandas.read_html, processes it to list the top 10 economies, and saves to a CSV file.</p>
          <p>- Dependencies: numpy, pandas.</p>
